{
  "mcpServers": {
    "onyx-enhanced": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/onyx_mcp/src/server.js"],
      "env": {
        "GITHUB_TOKEN": "your_github_token_here_optional"
      }
    }
  }
}

<!-- 
SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:

1. Replace "/path/to/onyx_mcp" with the actual path to your onyx_mcp directory
   Example: "/Users/username/Projects/onyx_mcp/src/server.js"

2. (Optional) Replace "your_github_token_here_optional" with your GitHub personal access token
   - This increases API rate limits for GitHub crawling
   - You can remove the entire "env" section if you don't want to use a token

3. Add this configuration to your Claude Desktop config file:
   - macOS: ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
   - Windows: %APPDATA%/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json

4. Before first use, populate the data:
   cd /path/to/onyx_mcp
   npm run crawl:all

5. Restart Claude Desktop

EXAMPLE USAGE IN CLAUDE:
- "Search for Onyx struct syntax"
- "Show me networking examples from GitHub"
- "Find HTTP client code in Onyx"
- "Crawl this tutorial: https://example.com/onyx-guide"
- "Search all sources for async examples"
-->
